      <akn:section eId="sec_2_218_52">
        <akn:num>2-218.52</akn:num>
        <akn:heading>Enforcement mechanism against an agency.</akn:heading>
<akn:subsection eId="subsec_2-218_52_a">
      <akn:num>(a)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>If an agency fails to meet any of the goals set forth in § 2-218.41, the Department may require that a portion of the agency’s contracts and procurements be made part of a set-aside program for small business enterprises.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_2-218_52_b">
      <akn:num>(b)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>The performance plan for each agency shall include a metric for compliance with the provisions of this subchapter and the performance evaluation for each agency director shall reflect the agency’s success in meeting compliance goals.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection>
      </akn:section>
